cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper presents a visual analytics interface to interpret the internal memory of an agent trained using deep reinforcement learning. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence. 
2. cs.LG - The paper deals with deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. 
3. cs.HC - The paper discusses the use of a visual analytics interface to assist experts in interpreting the memory of an agent. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction. 
4. cs.CV - The paper uses video game simulators to test the DRLViz interface, which involves processing visual data. This falls under the category of computer vision. 
5. cs.RO - The paper deals with navigation scenarios and item gathering tasks, which are common problems in robotics. This falls under the category of robotics.
